{{about|Russian and Soviet chess composer|Russian and Soviet footballer|Aleksei Troitsky (footballer)}} [[File:Troitzky.jpg|thumb|right|200px|A. A. Troitsky]]
'''Alexey Alexeyevich Troitsky''', or '''Alexei''', '''Troitzky''', or '''Troitzki''' ({{lang-ru|Алексе́й Алексе́евич Тро́ицкий}}) (March 14, 1866&ndash;August 1942) is considered to have been one of the greatest [[chess composer|composer]]s of [[chess]] [[endgame studies]].<ref>In the introduction to ''Collection of Chess Studies'', [[Sam Sloan]] writes "... Trotzky is considered to have been the greatest composer of chess endgame studies ever."</ref> He is widely regarded as the founder of the modern art of composing chess studies {{harvcol|Seirawan|2003|p=91}}. Troitsky died of [[starvation]] during [[World War II]] at the [[siege of Leningrad]], where his notes were destroyed.
One of his most famous works involves analyzing the [[Chess endgame|endgame]] with two knights versus a pawn, see [[Two knights endgame#Troitzky line|Troitsky line]]. [[John Nunn]] analyzed this endgame with an [[endgame tablebase]] and stated that "the analysis of Troitsky ... is astonishingly accurate" {{harvcol|Nunn|1995|p=265}}.
==Compositions== {{algebraic notation|pos=secright}} Troitsky was a prolific composer of endgame studies. [[Irving Chernev]] included nine of them in his book ''200 Brilliant Endgames''. The diagram shows one of them. {{Chess diagram |tleft | '''Troitsky, 1909''' | |qd| | | | | | | | |nd| | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |nl| | |kd| | | | | | | | | | |ql| | | | |kl| | | | | | | | | | | | |White to move and win }} The main line goes: :'''1. Nb6! Qe8''' :'''2. Nd7! Kc4''' :'''3. Qxc7+ Kb4''' :'''4. Qc5+ Kb3''' :'''5. Qc3+ Ka4''' :'''6. Qd4+ Ka3''' :'''7. Nc5 Qb8''' :'''8. Qa1+ Kb4''' :'''9. Na6+ and White wins {{harvcol|Chernev|1989|pp=207–8}}. {{clear}}
==Books== * Troitzky, A. (1924), ''500 Endspielstudien'', Verlag Kagan Berlin *{{Citation |surname1=Troitzky|given1=A. A. |year=1968 |title=360 Brilliant and Instructive End Games |publisher=[[Dover Publications]] (reprint) |isbn=0-486-21959-3}} * Troitzky, A. (1992), ''Collection of Studies'', Tschaturanga Ed. Olms, {{ISBN|3-283-00114-6}}. Reprinted in 2006 by [[Ishi Press]], {{ISBN|0-923891-10-2}}. The 360 studies above plus a supplement on the theory of the endgame of two knights against pawns.
