====Left-handed with strings backwards==== These are left-handed players who play naturally too, but with the strings organized to emulate an unaltered right-handed guitar, thus the strings are backwards for a left-handed player (e.g. Bob Geldof). Some players in this category (e.g. Dick Dale and Albert King) had custom instruments that were essentially left-handed guitars with the strings as on a right-handed guitar, since they had learned to play that way.
