'''Lucius Appuleius''' (fl. 4th century BCE) was a man of [[ancient Rome]] who served as [[Tribune of the Plebs]] in 391 BCE. He impeached [[Marcus Furius Camillus]] for having secreted part of the spoils of war against the rival [[Etruria|Etrurian]] city of [[Veii]] in 406.<ref>[[Livy]], ''[[Ab Urbe Condita Libri (Livy)|Ab Urbe Condita Libri]]'' 5. 32</ref><ref>[[Plutarch]], ''[http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Plut.%20Cam.%2012&lang=original Camillus]'' 12</ref>

